2 SENATE BILL 1003
1 (2025 Replacement Volume)
2 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
3 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
4 Article – Courts and Judicial Proceedings
5 2–327.
6 (b) [(1)] The Sheriff of Howard County shall receive:
7 [(i) An annual salary of $109,000 for calendar year 2021; and
8 (ii)] (1) For calendar year 2022 [and each subsequent] THROUGH
9 calendar year 2026, an annual salary equal to the salary of a major on step 6 of the Howard
10 County Police Management Schedule for the first year of the Sheriff’s term[.];
11 (2) [The salary of the Sheriff shall increase annually, according to the
12 Howard County Police Management Schedule, for as long as the individual holds the
13 position of Sheriff] AN ANNUAL SALARY OF $220,601 FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2027;
14 (3) AN ANNUAL SALARY OF $227,230 FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2028;
15 (4) AN ANNUAL SALARY OF $234,079 FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2029; AND
16 (5) AN ANNUAL SALARY OF $241,149 FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2030 AND
17 EACH SUBSEQUENT CALENDAR YEAR.
18 Article – Criminal Procedure
19 15–414.
20 (a) This section applies only in Howard County.
21 (b) The ANNUAL State’s Attorney’s salary is [equal]:
22 (1) EQUAL to the salary of a judge of the District Court of Maryland FOR
23 CALENDAR YEAR 2026;
24 (2) $220,601 FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2027;
25 (3) $227,230 FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2028;
26 (4) $234,079 FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2029; AND

SENATE BILL 1003 3
1 (5) $241,149 FOR CALENDAR YEAR 2030 AND EACH SUBSEQUENT
2 CALENDAR YEAR.
3 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, in accordance with Article
4 III, § 35 of the Maryland Constitution, this Act may not be construed to extend or apply to
5 the salary or compensation of the Sheriff of Howard County or the State’s Attorney of
6 Howard County while serving in a term of office beginning before the effective date of this
7 Act, but the provisions of this Act concerning the salary or compensation of the Sheriff of
8 Howard County or the State’s Attorney of Howard County shall take effect at the beginning
9 of the next following term of office. This limitation does not apply to an individual appointed
10 or elected after the effective date of this Act to fill out an unexpired term.
11 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
12 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
